===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|crūdēlis||hard, severe, cruel}}, akin to {{m|la|crūdus||raw, crude}}; see {{m|en|crude}}.

====Adjective====
{{en-adj|crueler|crueller|more}}

# Not [[nice]]; [[mean]]; [[heartless]].
#: ''The supervisor was very '''cruel''' to Josh, as he would always give Josh the hardest, most degrading work he could find.''
# {{lb|en|slang}} [[cool|Cool]]; [[awesome]]; [[neat]].

=====Usage notes=====
The word has metaphorical uses, for example "[[wikipedia:Emyn Muil|The cliffs]] remained cruel." (i.e. unclimbable when they desperately needed to be climbed) in ''[[wikipedia:The Lord of the Rings|The Lord of the Rings]]''.

